column1: Name of the new Print Format
Names and surnames by themselves are easy to guess.

Naming Options:\n
  1. field:[fieldname] - By Field
  2. naming_series: - By Naming Series (field called naming_series must be present
  3. Prompt - Prompt user for a name
  4. [series] - Series by prefix (separated by a dot); for example PRE.#####
    5. \n
  5. format:EXAMPLE-{MM}morewords{fieldname1}-{fieldname2}-{#####} - Replace all braced words (fieldnames, date words (DD, MM, YY), series) with their value. Outside braces, any characters can be used.
column2:
Amahitamo yo Kwita Izina:
  1. umurima: [izina ryumurima] - Na Field
  2. kwita izina_ibibazo: - Kubyita Urutonde (umurima witwa izina_series ugomba kuba uhari
  3. Byihuse - Bwira umukoresha izina
  4. [urukurikirane] - Urukurikirane rwibisobanuro (bitandukanijwe n'akadomo); kurugero PRE. #####
  5. imiterere: URUGERO- {MM} amagambo menshi {izina ryumwanya1} - {umurima2} - {#####} - Simbuza amagambo yose afatanye (amazina yumurima , amagambo yitariki (DD, MM, YY), urukurikirane) nagaciro kabo. Hanze yinyuguti, inyuguti zose zirashobora gukoreshwa.
